UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS - BANGLADESH (SYLHET)
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 26 June 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Cosmos (United News Of Bangladesh) 22 Jun 2001 [edited]

SYLHET: At least 13 people died of viral fever in different villages
of Ronikhai union in Companiganj upazila last week, health officials
said today. Particularly women and children are vulnerable to the
viral fever spreading at epidemic proportions.
The dead in Banpur village were aged 24, 9 (2 cases), 7 (2 cases), and
9 months; and in Ronikhai Adarsha village females aged 35 and 30 and
children aged 5 (2 cases), 3 months (2 cases) and one month old.
The worst affected by the scourge are Lamagram, Banpur, Majhergaon,
Kamalbasti, Batumara, Khupriparh, Turang and Jangail. Currently 2
medical teams, one led by Dr Gopal Chandra Roy and another by Dr
Zubair, have been working in the areas carrying out test on blood of
the patients, said a health official. "We have so far carried out
tests on the blood of 30 patients, but no one was diagnosed as
malarial patient," he said.
